File: ANC Stephane de Sakutin / AFP JOHANNESBURG - After a scathing SIU report was released on Friday around PPE corruption, former Gauteng health MEC Bandile Masuku and suspended presidential spokesperson Khusela Diko are facing their disciplinary proceedings on Saturday. READ: PPE Tenders: Contracts worth R13.3bn to be investigated The proceedings come on the back of their alleged role in PPE corruption and other tender irregularities. Masuku, his wife Loyiso, and Diko were summoned before the party's integrity commission in July last year. Masuku has been replaced as Health MEC while Diko is on special leave. ANC Gauteng Secretary, Jacob Khawe said the decision outcomes should be concluded later this month.